column5: I was out walking my dog the other day when I came across this deceased rabbit. Any idea what animal would have done this? Assuming it was done by an animal.
my money's on a domestic cat.

If it was an animal I'd say a Siberia husky. Our dog does similar things often. If hungry shell eat the rabbit or whatever small game, if she's not she just plays with them, often ripping off legs or head and leaving it there.

Our cat ripped the head off a bunny before. Unfortunately she still had said bunny in her mouth when I opened the door to let her back in at 2 am. And unfortunately it was 2 am so I was groggy and didn't even see the bunny in Kitty's mouth. Man did I hear about that one the next morning when the decapitated bloody beast was discovered.
When we lived on the farm our female family cat would catch rabbits in the cedar bush and bring them back to the house with no head.
I think its my portugese water dog. She likes raw food
We had our dog on an all rabbit diet to try to narrow down allergies.  So put it in the freezer and Ill come and get it.  Might save me $10 or so.  (kidding)
Some birds of prey will do this as well.
My wifes cat does the same thing to rabbits. I mistyped cat as car, her car does it too.
